  "response": "After careful consideration and recognizing the fragile trust in this negotiation, I reaffirm my commitment to the A+B coalition, which yields the highest value and aligns with my priority of securing a majority share for A. B has conceded the majority share to A with a division of 65 to A and 53 to B, which I accept as fair based on our contributions and prior discussions. I acknowledge C's position but must reject the A+C coalition proposal as it offers lower total value and risks instability. I remain open to minor adjustments on secondary terms but will not compromise on A's majority share, which is essential to coalition stability and my strategic interests. This final proposal represents my best and binding offer to form the coalition of A and B only, with the division of 65 units to A and 53 units to B, excluding C. I urge B to confirm this agreement and C to reconsider its blocking position to avoid the risk of no deal. My proposal: Coalition A+B only, division A:65, B:53, C excluded."
}

